article.headline: Dartmouth 65, New Hampshire 60
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Dartmouth's Alex Barnett hit a jump shot with two seconds left in regulation to send the game into overtime, and the Big Green went on a 8-1 run in the extra period to beat New Hampshire 65-60 Tuesday night in their intrastate rivalry. Barnett's basket capped a 15-5 run that pulled Dartmouth from behind a 49-39 deficit with 4:16 remaining. Trailing 59-57 in overtime, Marlon Sanders tied it for Dartmouth (7-8) and Jonathan Ball hit a layup to put the Big Green ahead to stay, 61-59. They iced the game with four free throws in the final seconds. Barnett led three Dartmouth players in double digits with 13 points and 12 rebounds. Tyrece Gibbs scored 21 points and seven rebounds for New Hampshire (4-12).
